I feel like I was given
one last chance

16:44.253 --> 16:46.255
and it got yanked away.

16:46.255 --> 16:47.965
Mitchell was furious.

16:47.965 --> 16:52.094
Gordon just kept going
and going. It's over, Dot.

16:52.094 --> 16:55.264
I'm going to be stuck at Mullen
for the rest of my life.

16:55.264 --> 16:58.642
On the bright side,
we're done with Herr Liddy.

16:58.642 --> 17:00.936
Welcome home, Papa.

17:00.936 --> 17:04.273
We're jamming at Sully's.
You want to come?

17:04.273 --> 17:06.191
Doesn't that sound like fun,
Papa?

17:06.191 --> 17:07.651
That is absolutely

17:07.651 --> 17:10.738
the last thing
my splitting headache needs.

17:10.738 --> 17:14.366
- Good luck, kiddo.
- Sure, whatever. It's fine.

17:14.366 --> 17:16.618
You'll get another chance, honey.

17:16.618 --> 17:21.039
I would love to see your band.
Are you taking requests?

17:21.957 --> 17:23.208
- Mom.
- Yeah?

17:23.208 --> 17:24.960
We're not playing
MacArthur Park.

17:24.960 --> 17:26.170
Come on!

17:27.880 --> 17:30.507
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:35.429 --> 17:39.016
Mr. Hunt! Mr. Liddy wants you
to read Jack Anderson's column

17:39.016 --> 17:40.559
and call him immediately.

17:40.559 --> 17:42.770
Mr. Liddy
can go fuck himself.

17:43.979 --> 17:45.063
<i>Good evening.</i>

17:45.063 --> 17:47.608
<i>Charges made by newspaper
columnist Jack Anderson</i>

17:47.608 --> 17:50.444
<i>have raised grave questions
about the integrity</i>

17:50.444 --> 17:51.862
<i>of the Nixon administration.</i>

17:51.862 --> 17:53.822
<i>Anderson wrote today
that he has evidence</i>

17:53.822 --> 17:56.450
<i>that the International Telephone
and Telegraph company</i>

17:56.450 --> 17:58.786
<i>made a secret deal
with the administration</i>

17:58.786 --> 18:02.790
<i>to obtain a favorable settlement
